{
  "doc_id": "25211",
  "text": "The deadwood decomposition is dependent on many factors including tree species, temperature, moisture and substrate quality [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Wood chemistry, e.g. content of lignin or C:N ratio, and other species-species traits can have a significant influence on the rates of decomposition [CITATION_3] ). According to [CITATION_4] , the slower decay of lignin compared to cellulose suggested that lignin could be an important long-term source of soil organic carbon and that this process could be greatly affected by forest species mixtures.",
